result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Annie M Olen was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Annie M Olen was found guilty of Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. ADDRESS INFO for Annie M Olen
Current: 3561 S. HONEY CREEK DR., Milwaukee, WI 53220-1246 United States  (Effective: 03-09-2016)
Prior: 130 West Rainbow Ridge Drive, #611, Oak Creek, WI 53154

Defendant Annie M Olen in court with attorney Christina E. Balistreri.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  AS TO COUNT #1 & COUNT #3:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT #1: Court ordered defendant to serve 5 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for (3) days time served with Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED sentence until 4-21-2015.  
Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $350.00 plus all applicable costs and surcharges to be paid by 10-13-2015. If unpaid, a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant. 
Defendant to provide DNA specimen and pay mandatory DNA surcharge by 10-13-2015.   If unpaid, a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant. 
Defendant is advised that they may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if they meet the conditions under Wis. Stats. section 165. 77(4).,
Court ordered defendant's operating privileges are revoked for a period of 12 months.
Court ordered ignition interlock for a period of 12 months, with $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge ordered.
Court ordered defendant to obtain an alcohol assessment.
AS TO COUNT #2:  By operation of law, Court ordered Ct. #2 DISMISSED.
AS TO COUNT #3:  Court ordered defendant to serve 5 days in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to any other sentence, with credit for (3) days time served with Huber privileges for work.  Court STAYED sentence until 4-21-2015.  
Defendant to provide DNA specimen and pay mandatory DNA surcharge by 10-13-2015.   If unpaid, a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant. 
Defendant is advised that they may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if they meet the conditions under Wis. Stats. section 165. 77(4).,  Court WAIVED any further costs or surcharges due to defendant's financial situation.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Deputy Court Clerk jks
